div.div: How do I install ruby gems on Mac

I would highly suggest using a package manager and a Ruby Environment Manager. On Mac: brew update brew install ruby (6 more lines were trimmed) You can do that but I suggest using an Environment Manager for Ruby. You have rbenv and RVM.
IMO go for rbenv: brew install rbenv ruby-build
